I like the band! I think the band is good.

01:09:05.875 --> 01:09:09.755
But what they did should have been left
behind closed doors!

01:09:09.917 --> 01:09:16.175
America is a much more puritanical country
and we, our sex is sort of kept hidden.

01:09:16.332 --> 01:09:19.542
Which is strange because we are
the porn capital of the world,

01:09:19.707 --> 01:09:21.176
but we're a puritanical country.

01:09:21.332 --> 01:09:25.133
I believe we did have to send documents
just saying that it was all simulated,

01:09:25.292 --> 01:09:29.001
that there was no actual nudity and
there was no actual sex on stage.

01:09:29.167 --> 01:09:31.340
Yeah, just dumb, dumb stuff.

01:09:38.792 --> 01:09:40.135
Our Doggy here

01:09:43.167 --> 01:09:48.048
is scared to go back to jail,
back to the big, bad people.

01:09:49.250 --> 01:09:51.627
We had to get used
to a lot of things in America.

01:09:51.792 --> 01:09:54.341
Because we know it as the Land of Freedom,

01:09:54.500 --> 01:09:57.379
the land of dishwashers
who become millionaires.

01:09:57.542 --> 01:10:00.466
I always thought
you could do what you wanted here.

01:10:00.625 --> 01:10:03.094
It's crazy when a bit of
fun turns so serious.

01:10:03.250 --> 01:10:06.333
As a band, you feel pretty untouchable.

01:10:06.500 --> 01:10:09.049
You're the king, everyone
thinks you're great,

01:10:09.050 --> 01:10:14.970
people ﬂatter you. You're driven around,
and your every wish is catered for.

01:10:15.750 --> 01:10:20.210
Then suddenly
you're not the king anymore,

01:10:20.375 --> 01:10:22.798
you're hardly anything.

01:10:22.958 --> 01:10:27.043
Yeah, but since then you have a record,
and every time they enter the country

01:10:27.208 --> 01:10:28.835
they both have to be interviewed.

01:10:29.167 --> 01:10:31.465
We just wait. We have two shuttles,

01:10:31.625 --> 01:10:35.084
so the band is comfortably in the hotel
while Till and Flake

01:10:35.085 --> 01:10:38.713
get to sit there for another hour
and be harassed.

01:10:38.875 --> 01:10:42.334
I can't get used to the fact that you
can't just pee against a tree somewhere.

01:10:42.500 --> 01:10:45.253
I was put in a paddy wagon in Texas

01:10:45.417 --> 01:10:50.041
because I pissed between two bins
at the exit behind the stage.

01:10:50.042 --> 01:10:53.999
And then it went off!
You're in my country, in my city,

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:57.209
this is my district
and you won't be peeing anywhere!

01:10:57.375 --> 01:11:00.754
Just don't talk back, otherwise
you'll end up in jail immediately!

01:11:00.958 --> 01:11:04.542
And that, to me, is a bit more restrictive
to personal freedom

01:11:04.708 --> 01:11:06.631
than what we're used to in Europe.

01:11:06.792 --> 01:11:08.669
Since then, we're very humble,

01:11:08.833 --> 01:11:11.052
even the fire marshal gets fawned over,

01:11:11.208 --> 01:11:13.802
because you can't allow
yourself any mistakes.

01:11:13.958 --> 01:11:17.667
The so-called authorities here,
they have such power!

01:11:17.833 --> 01:11:20.507
They can send you home overnight.

01:11:20.708 --> 01:11:24.258
They revoke your work permit
or cancel the concert,

01:11:24.417 --> 01:11:28.126
you go to jail or just
pay a ridiculous fine.

01:11:28.292 --> 01:11:34.459
If something challenging and shocking
is not a product, you'll be punished.

01:11:34.625 --> 01:11:36.593
But if it becomes a product,

01:11:36.750 --> 01:11:39.253
“Oh yeah, they're doing that
in Madison Square Garden,

01:11:39.417 --> 01:11:42.546
I wanna go see that giant
penis right now!“.

01:13:19.750 --> 01:13:23.505
In 1999 'Rammstein'
tour Latin America with 'Kiss.'

01:13:25.167 --> 01:13:26.082
Myth,

01:13:26.083 --> 01:13:27.050
Power,

01:13:27.208 --> 01:13:28.130
Excess,

01:13:28.333 --> 01:13:29.334
Eroticism,

01:13:29.708 --> 01:13:33.793
The most perfect German machine in Mexico.

01:13:36.417 --> 01:13:38.840
The rest is history.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:41.549
Tickets on sale now!

01:13:44.417 --> 01:13:47.261
They still built Beetles here,
you can tell straight away!

01:13:49.583 --> 01:13:51.335
There, another Beetle!

01:13:51.500 --> 01:13:53.047
One, two, three Beetles.

01:13:53.208 --> 01:13:56.257
I'll tell you when I see
a Beetle, Schneider.

01:14:00.542 --> 01:14:02.715
There's a press conference this evening.

01:14:03.042 --> 01:14:07.127
Who is taking part in the press conference?

01:14:07.292 --> 01:14:09.636
All of us!

01:14:11.583 --> 01:14:13.460
Right after that...

01:14:13.625 --> 01:14:17.584
After the press conference?
There are going to be free records again.

01:14:18.000 --> 01:14:20.999
- Where 30 selected...
- CDs

01:14:21.000 --> 01:14:23.753
listeners can get their CDs signed.

01:14:29.417 --> 01:14:32.011
Quickly, run along the wall!
As fast as you can!

01:14:32.583 --> 01:14:35.837
We drove there in a shuttle
and thought there's a protest going on,

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:39.709
we have to get around it somehow.
Then the driver said it was because of us!

01:14:39.875 --> 01:14:41.627
And then there was complete panic.

01:14:41.792 --> 01:14:45.751
We had to get into this record store
within three, four minutes.

01:14:45.917 --> 01:14:49.467
They closed the shutters behind us and the
people crushed themselves against it!

01:14:49.625 --> 01:14:52.834
All the roads were blocked!
People were standing on buildings.

01:15:01.833 --> 01:15:04.131
Then the chief of police
came to us and said:

01:15:04.292 --> 01:15:08.217
If you don't go onto the roof
and say something to calm people down,

01:15:08.375 --> 01:15:11.424
because they're taking the ﬂower
boxes apart on the boulevard,

01:15:11.583 --> 01:15:12.835
then you'll be arrested!

01:15:13.000 --> 01:15:15.048
And I said, how is this our fault?

01:15:15.208 --> 01:15:18.337
Well, this is all because of you!
He was really angry!

01:15:18.500 --> 01:15:24.428
So we went onto the roof and yelled
through the megaphone in jumbled Spanish.

01:15:24.583 --> 01:15:26.551
There were people everywhere!

01:15:26.708 --> 01:15:29.336
The parking garage opposite
was stuffed with people.

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:40.469
And when Till took the
megaphone in his hand

01:15:40.625 --> 01:15:43.048
and shouted something to the masses,

01:15:43.208 --> 01:15:46.838
and they screamed,
there was this feeling of, OK!

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:54.794
You can say anything here, they'll scream
and think we're great regardless.

01:15:54.958 --> 01:15:58.041
That was the first time we realized
the kind of responsibility

01:15:58.208 --> 01:16:00.552
we carry in what we do.

01:16:00.708 --> 01:16:02.802
Then we went down again and left.

01:16:09.167 --> 01:16:11.261
Do I have everything? Did they rob me?

01:16:15.000 --> 01:16:18.083
Something like that
never happened to us before!

01:16:18.250 --> 01:16:21.094
And it was so out of the blue!
We thought we were just going

01:16:21.250 --> 01:16:23.844
to an autograph session,
and suddenly there was a riot.

01:16:24.000 --> 01:16:27.209
People don't believe us
when we tell them that people in Mexico

01:16:27.375 --> 01:16:31.084
sing along twice as loudly as in Germany,
where we actually come from.

01:16:31.085 --> 01:16:35.884
I remember that, in Mexico, entire families
came to the concert, with kids and everything.

01:16:59.083 --> 01:17:01.427
What left a lasting impression on me was

01:17:01.583 --> 01:17:07.750
that the Mexican audience was
fully outfitted in T-shirts we didn't make!

01:17:07.917 --> 01:17:12.627
They had unbelievably cool designs
and were graphically very interesting.

01:17:12.792 --> 01:17:17.844
Only later did we realize that they
just have their own market for it there.

01:17:34.208 --> 01:17:39.214
There was a street
with a merchandise shop on each side.

01:17:39.375 --> 01:17:40.752
I've never seen anything like it!

01:17:40.917 --> 01:17:43.340
They had 'Rammstein'
merchandise, and they sell it there.

01:17:43.500 --> 01:17:45.468
Everything that you could possibly imagine,

01:17:45.833 --> 01:17:49.004
everything you need for your household,
had 'Rammstein' on it.

01:17:49.005 --> 01:17:52.504
That's what they sold.
It was cheap, but they had everything!

01:17:57.000 --> 01:18:01.756
The tour takes 'Rammstein' to the city of
Teotihuacan in the Mexican high plains,

01:18:02.042 --> 01:18:05.041
one of America's most significant ruins.

01:18:05.042 --> 01:18:10.094
Named by the Aztecs, the place
translates as "where man becomes god."

01:18:12.208 --> 01:18:14.427
It's really exhausting!

01:18:20.792 --> 01:18:26.674
I fell something like three meters
on the last pyramid and sprained my leg.

01:18:31.792 --> 01:18:35.092
How did that happen? You wanted to jump up
somewhere? Or jump down?

01:18:35.250 --> 01:18:38.174
I wanted to climb down
normally, I just fell.

01:18:38.333 --> 01:18:44.215
Then during the show, because we still
had to play, I was getting shots

01:18:44.375 --> 01:18:46.377
so that it wouldn't hurt so much!

01:19:09.083 --> 01:19:11.211
The thing about South America is,

01:19:11.375 --> 01:19:14.002
it's great audiences,
but very difficult to tour.

01:19:14.003 --> 01:19:17.300
Because you have to ship,
ﬂy everything from city to city,

01:19:17.458 --> 01:19:20.047
you can't just put it
in trucks and let it go

01:19:20.048 --> 01:19:23.376
because you don't know if it's going
to show up at the other end.

01:19:25.500 --> 01:19:29.505
So, for the most part.
Also the distances are so great, too.

01:19:29.667 --> 01:19:31.385
So you have to airfreight stuff.

01:19:35.375 --> 01:19:39.505
The South American tour
also takes in Argentina and Brazil.

01:19:46.125 --> 01:19:48.753
The shared concerts
with 'Kiss' in South America

01:19:48.917 --> 01:19:51.295
are a particular highlight for 'Rammstein.'

01:20:02.000 --> 01:20:07.962
I remember the first concert in Buenos
Aires, Argentina, as they came out.

01:20:08.125 --> 01:20:11.459
And suddenly I ran after them
like a little kid

01:20:11.625 --> 01:20:15.255
and reverted back to my 14-year-old self.

01:20:15.417 --> 01:20:18.341
Because there were,
like I said, these little pictures

01:20:18.500 --> 01:20:22.300
that you could buy for something like
20 deutschmarks on the school corner,

01:20:23.167 --> 01:20:25.215
and I would stare
at these pictures constantly,

01:20:25.375 --> 01:20:28.629
with intense fantasies
running through my head.

01:20:28.792 --> 01:20:33.468
I thought their appearance, their makeup
and style was totally awesome!

01:20:34.667 --> 01:20:40.345
If we are in any way responsible
for giving them the inspiration,

01:20:40.667 --> 01:20:42.089
it's something to be proud of!

01:20:42.250 --> 01:20:46.380
They are out there,
maybe if they weren't a band,

01:20:46.542 --> 01:20:50.172
they would be burning houses down,
so we keep them on stage.

01:20:52.708 --> 01:20:55.757
I think 'Rammstein' seems
like a German band.

01:20:55.917 --> 01:21:00.297
They've got something about them,
there's a vibe, the great pyro.

01:21:00.458 --> 01:21:02.836
These guys, I heard that a couple
of the guys in the band

01:21:03.000 --> 01:21:05.628
are actually professional pyrotechnicians.

01:21:05.792 --> 01:21:09.251
So, they do that very uniquely and
it's over the top!

01:21:09.417 --> 01:21:12.842
And anything like that, any band like that
definitely appeals to us as well,

01:21:13.000 --> 01:21:17.881
even though they probably got some of
their stuff originally from this band!

01:21:21.833 --> 01:21:26.043
At some point, I remember, I was on stage
with Oli, there was a moment -

01:21:26.044 --> 01:21:29.717
you never saw them, those guys,
because they always had makeup on -

01:21:29.875 --> 01:21:32.045
we were standing there looking at them,

01:21:32.046 --> 01:21:35.797
and then Paul Stanley turned around
during the concert and went like this.

01:21:37.667 --> 01:21:41.922
Or I was with Schneider,
and I was like: WOW!

01:21:47.667 --> 01:21:52.844
However, the band find out first hand just
how unforgiving the 'Kiss Army' can be.

01:22:06.667 --> 01:22:13.050
We've never experienced so much hate
from the audience as we did in Sao Paulo.

01:22:13.208 --> 01:22:16.257
When we came on stage,
they thought 'Kiss' was starting.

01:22:16.417 --> 01:22:18.340
And then some German idiots appeared

01:22:18.500 --> 01:22:20.969
and started to play things
no one could understand.

01:22:21.125 --> 01:22:24.004
Of course they lost it
and started throwing things at us,

01:22:24.005 --> 01:22:27.209
lighters, small bottles, rocks.

01:22:27.375 --> 01:22:31.676
It was a nightmare!
I think it was the worst concert ever!

01:22:49.000 --> 01:22:51.844
At the end, the event organizer
even said to us, I remember

01:22:52.000 --> 01:22:56.380
you should be glad
they didn't throw half a goat at you.

01:22:56.542 --> 01:22:59.011
That's normal. You did well.

01:23:09.708 --> 01:23:12.086
After the South American tour
it will be two years

01:23:12.250 --> 01:23:16.881
before 'Rammstein' tour North America
again, with the new album "Mutter.“".

01:23:27.208 --> 01:23:30.087
The one mistake I think a lot of
European artists make

01:23:30.250 --> 01:23:34.084
when they come to the States,
is they forget how big it is.

01:23:34.542 --> 01:23:37.796
And like a lot of European artists
will come to the States to tour

01:23:37.958 --> 01:23:41.758
and play ten shows and think that's a tour.

01:23:41.958 --> 01:23:44.586
Whereas, you look at some
of these American artists

01:23:44.750 --> 01:23:47.219
like 'Kid Rock'
or 'Dave Matthews' or whomever,

01:23:47.500 --> 01:23:50.583
they play 200 shows in America every year.

01:24:11.625 --> 01:24:13.844
'Rammstein' play more than 40 concerts,

01:24:14.042 --> 01:24:18.627
27 of them in 4 weeks on their headlining
summer tour, and a further 20 in autumn -

01:24:19.250 --> 01:24:22.379
a punishingly tight schedule
for everyone involved.

01:24:25.208 --> 01:24:31.011
It was so tedious, because you spend time
in so many areas that aren't very exciting.

01:24:31.208 --> 01:24:35.258
Of course, New York is interesting,
and San Francisco is nice and so is LA.

01:24:43.125 --> 01:24:44.752
I loved New Orleans.

01:24:44.917 --> 01:24:49.673
It had an extremely dark appeal
when I was there,

01:24:49.833 --> 01:24:52.507
but a very interesting appeal.

01:24:53.542 --> 01:24:58.093
The West Coast, San Francisco
and Seattle were really cool.

01:24:58.417 --> 01:25:02.297
L.A., of course, but everything around
that was quite difficult.

01:25:25.458 --> 01:25:29.383
In July alone they perform
in a different city almost every day,

01:25:29.708 --> 01:25:31.506
traversing the entire country.

01:25:31.792 --> 01:25:36.673
The enormous distances covered can't fail
to leave an impression on the musicians.

01:25:42.583 --> 01:25:45.962
Most hard rock bands are on the road
for like 2 years straight,

01:25:46.125 --> 01:25:49.675
they have no life and no body,
'cause they just tour nonstop.

01:25:49.833 --> 01:25:53.667
When you are an American band
touring the U.S. for two years,

01:25:53.833 --> 01:25:56.952
you're like a heartless
soul, it's disgusting.

01:25:56.978 --> 01:25:59.035
It's a terrible place to tour.

01:26:20.250 --> 01:26:23.709
The toughest time really is
being away from your friends and family.

01:26:23.875 --> 01:26:27.459
And a lot of the times
when you're on the road for a long time,

01:26:27.625 --> 01:26:29.753
you kind of stay the same.

01:26:29.917 --> 01:26:34.002
Like the band, we're still the same people
even if we're gone for 5 or 6 months.

01:26:34.167 --> 01:26:36.420
But you get home and things have changed.

01:26:36.833 --> 01:26:43.041
Really weird things happen, like they
forget you at home. You're a stranger!

01:26:43.042 --> 01:26:45.033
I think that's the
most difficult point,

01:26:45.059 --> 01:26:47.243
it's re-adjusting to
life once you get home.

01:26:50.250 --> 01:26:52.548
'Rammstein' miss the old days...

01:26:55.792 --> 01:26:57.590
Now everyone has their own hotel room,

01:26:57.750 --> 01:27:00.089
we don't see each other,
it's actually boring.

01:27:00.090 --> 01:27:02.677
In general, it's better like that
for such a long tour,

01:27:02.833 --> 01:27:07.760
but sometimes you long for how it was back
when we all drove around in a little bus

01:27:07.917 --> 01:27:11.717
and had a plate with sandwiches,
which was the food for the entire day.

01:27:11.875 --> 01:27:15.084
As far as the atmosphere goes,
it was somehow better than now.

01:27:15.085 --> 01:27:17.757
We were more like a band,
we kind of lived together.

01:27:17.917 --> 01:27:21.091
Back then, Till used to go
to the petrol station and steal food.

01:27:21.092 --> 01:27:24.212
We'd rip open the bags
in the bus and eat it.

01:27:24.417 --> 01:27:27.546
It was fun, and there was
a good feeling among us.

01:27:27.750 --> 01:27:31.630
Now you just order room service,
it's not a lifestyle!

01:27:33.667 --> 01:27:37.044
What preceded the 2001
'Pledge of Allegiance' tour,

01:27:37.045 --> 01:27:39.136
with Slipknot' and 'System of a Down, '

01:27:39.292 --> 01:27:42.967
remains stamped in memory
far beyond 'Rammstein.'

01:28:01.458 --> 01:28:04.587
This was the apartment
of my then-girlfriend,

01:28:04.750 --> 01:28:08.755
and it's also where I
witnessed September 11.

01:28:08.917 --> 01:28:16.051
At around 9 am, a friend phoned me
from Europe.

01:28:16.208 --> 01:28:20.668
I was lying in bed,
and she wondered if I was OK.

01:28:20.833 --> 01:28:22.631
I didn't understand what she meant

01:28:22.792 --> 01:28:25.796
because I thought
she was asking if I had arrived safely.

01:28:25.958 --> 01:28:28.086
Then she said, no! You have to get out!

01:28:28.087 --> 01:28:33.044
So I Raft here and went around the corner.

01:28:33.208 --> 01:28:39.011
That's where I saw
the second plane ﬂy into the second tower.

01:28:41.417 --> 01:28:43.670
The crew was in the air as it happened,

01:28:43.833 --> 01:28:50.041
and then they were rerouted to Montreal and
had to wait in a huge arena for two days,

01:28:50.042 --> 01:28:52.090
and were given crispy bread to eat.

01:29:03.750 --> 01:29:06.674
I remember the band being frustrated
after some of the shows

01:29:06.833 --> 01:29:09.712
because of the reaction,
was not what they expected.

01:29:18.208 --> 01:29:23.169
The extreme strain of recent years
takes its toll on the band on this tour.

01:29:23.625 --> 01:29:27.009
There are tensions between
Paul and Richard,

01:29:27.035 --> 01:29:29.817
and the atmosphere
hits rock bottom.

01:29:36.208 --> 01:29:39.587
The post-9/11 political
climate does not help.

01:29:42.208 --> 01:29:45.712
Everyone from the bus driver
to the cleaning lady was mobilized!

01:29:45.875 --> 01:29:49.960
Everyone wanted to bomb something,
wanted to find those responsible!

01:29:50.125 --> 01:29:53.425
We had this feeling, that sentiment
that existed all over Europe,

01:29:53.583 --> 01:29:57.258
that America was suddenly so strange
and not like it used to be.

01:29:57.417 --> 01:30:00.967
We weren't even talking to each other
from time to time,

01:30:01.125 --> 01:30:05.551
whatever. We often didn't talk
to each other anymore.

01:30:14.625 --> 01:30:20.177
Some of the band members
were very uneasy with 9/11.

01:30:20.333 --> 01:30:24.213
And one <i>m</i> particular
decided to call it quits

01:30:24.375 --> 01:30:28.960
and get on a plane and ﬂy out of JFK
and said bye bye.

01:30:29.125 --> 01:30:32.095
In the end, Flake just went home.

01:30:32.250 --> 01:30:35.880
Right! Now I remember.

01:30:36.458 --> 01:30:43.376
It was so bad for him
that he just left everything behind,

01:30:43.542 --> 01:30:47.422
went to the airport and ﬂew home.
He just threw in the towel.

01:30:47.625 --> 01:30:52.210
So you do notice that it's a certain...

01:30:52.417 --> 01:30:56.672
But I have to add that we
totally slipped into this wave of hysteria,

01:30:56.833 --> 01:31:02.966
and I found the frenzied atmosphere
very frightening.

01:31:04.792 --> 01:31:07.511
The whole of the USA is gripped by 9/11,

01:31:07.917 --> 01:31:11.717
with society paralyzed
by the fear of further terrorist attacks.

01:31:12.292 --> 01:31:15.091
The land of freedom
and limitless possibilities

01:31:15.333 --> 01:31:19.008
begins to turn in on itself
and loses some of its lustre.

01:31:19.792 --> 01:31:21.669
And it was sort of a dividing line.

01:31:21.833 --> 01:31:28.876
To me, that tour was were 'Rammstein' stopped
trying to force things to work in America

01:31:29.042 --> 01:31:33.843
and stopped playing by the rules
and just went away for a while and waited,

01:31:34.000 --> 01:31:38.631
whether by accident or design,
